<worksheet >
    <title>FUN-3 Vector Valued Functions</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>To earn an M on this outcome, you will need to correctly complete all three parts. To earn a P on this outcome, you will need to correctly complete 
        two parts with progress on the third.</p>
  </introduction>  
  <page>
    <exercise workspace="1.5in">
        <introduction><p>A particle is moving in space with a velocity (measured in m/s) of <m>\vec{v}(t) = \langle \sqrt{2}\cos(t),\sin(t),\sqrt{3} \rangle</m>.</p></introduction>
      <task><statement><p>Find the position vector of the particle,<m>\vec{r}(t)</m>, given that <m>\vec{r}(0) = \langle 2,4,0 \rangle</m>.</p></statement></task>
      <task><statement><p>Find the distance traveled by the particle from time <m>t=0</m> to time <m>t=2\pi</m>.</p></statement></task>
      <task><statement><p>Find the unit tangent vector of the particle at time <m>t=\pi</m>.</p></statement></task>
    </exercise>
  </page>
</worksheet>